  "method": {
    "_documentation": [
      "Penalty weights for graded-severity scoring.",
      "",
      "Per-pair severities in [0, 1] are computed for each issue",
      "(see issues.py and the module docstring of this script for",
      "the exact severity formulas), then mean-aggregated across",
      "the GOOD and POOR reference sets.",
      "",
      "LOG-ODDS ON MEAN SEVERITY:",
      "    s_good_i = (mean_sev_good_i × N_good + 1) / (N_good + 2)",
      "    s_poor_i = (mean_sev_poor_i × N_poor + 1) / (N_poor + 2)",
      "    raw_i    = max(0, ln(s_poor_i / s_good_i))",
      "    weight_i = raw_i / Σ raw_j × 100",
      "  Issues more severe in poor than good get high weight.",
      "  Issues at equal mean severity → 0. Issues more severe",
      "  in good are clipped to 0 (background variation).",
      "",
      "At runtime:",
      "    penalty = Σ penalty_weights[i] × severity[i]",
      "    score   = max(0, min(100, 100 − penalty))",
      "",
      "Reference: graded-severity principle from Cerny et al.",
      "NAR 2026. Continuous-parameter severity uses the paper's",
      "ProSco (KDE-based probability percentile score), replacing",
      "the earlier Z' linear ramp after Joe's 2026-05-19 review."
    ],
